Mango Airline to Use Johannesburg’s Lanseria Airport, Business Report Says

-- B y   A n t o n y   S g u a z z i n
-- 
2011-05-03T05:25:40Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-03/mango-airline-to-use-johannesburg-s-lanseria-airport-business-report-says.html
Mango, a low-cost subsidiary of South
African Airways Ltd., will start flights to  Cape Town  from
Johannesburg’s Lanseria airport from June 1, Business Report
said, citing a statement from the company.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Antony Sguazzin at 
 asguazzin@bloomberg.net  